(554, 60, 'Describe a scenario where you would use System Design principles to architect a scalable mobile application, and how you would apply Modular Architecture and Design Patterns to achieve this', 'No answer provided.', 'System Design', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Lack of understanding of System Design principles\", \"Inability to apply Modular Architecture and Design Patterns\", \"Failure to provide a scenario for scalable mobile application architecture\"]', '[\"Study and review System Design principles for mobile applications\", \"Research and practice applying Modular Architecture and Design Patterns in iOS development\", \"Prepare to describe a scenario where scalability is crucial and explain how to achieve it using industry-standard design principles and patterns\"]'),
(555, 60, 'How would you handle communication between modules in this architecture, and what mechanisms would you use to ensure loose coupling and high cohesion?', 'fine Kaushal pundamave', 'System Design', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Lack of understanding of system design principles\", \"Inability to articulate design decisions\", \"Failure to provide relevant technical terms or concepts\"]', '[\"Study iOS architecture patterns such as MVC, MVP, and MVVM\", \"Learn about dependency injection and service locators for loose coupling\", \"Research design principles like SOLID and apply them to iOS development\", \"Practice explaining technical concepts and design decisions clearly and concisely\"]'),
(556, 61, 'What is the difference between a LEFT JOIN and an INNER JOIN in MySQL, and when would you use each?', 'An INNER JOIN is used when you want to find the strict overlap between two tables, returning only the rows that have matching values in both. It acts as an exclusive filter, making it perfect for situations where incomplete records are unhelpful to your analysis, such as matching registered users with the actual finalized orders they have placed.\n\nIn contrast, a LEFT JOIN prioritizes the completeness of your primary table, returning every single row from the left side of your query regardless of whether a match exists on the right side. When a match is missing, the database simply fills in the blanks with NULL, which is incredibly useful for identifying missing relationships, like finding users who have created an account but haven\'t actually made a purchase yet.', 'MySQL', 90, '[\"correctly defines INNER JOIN\", \"correctly defines LEFT JOIN\", \"provides relevant use cases for each\"]', '[\"could provide more technical details about the joins\", \"could mention other types of joins for completeness\"]', '[\"review the differences between INNER, LEFT, RIGHT, and FULL OUTER JOINs to be familiar with all options\", \"practice explaining technical concepts in a clear and concise manner, focusing on relevance to iOS application development and potential database interactions\"]'),
(557, 61, 'Can you provide an example of a scenario where you would use a LEFT JOIN instead of an INNER JOIN?', 'The Scenario: A School Roster\nImagine you manage a school database and you need to generate a report showing every student in the school alongside the extracurricular club they belong to.\n\nHere are your two starting tables:\n\nTable 1: Students (The Left Table)\n| student_id | student_name |\n| :--- | :--- |\n| 1 | Alice |\n| 2 | Bob |\n| 3 | Charlie |\n| 4 | Diana |\n\nTable 2: Clubs (The Right Table)\n| student_id | club_name |\n| :--- | :--- |\n| 1 | Drama Club |\n| 2 | Chess Team |\n| 4 | Debate Society |\n\n(Notice that Charlie (student_id 3) hasn\'t joined any clubs yet, so he is entirely missing from the Clubs table).\n\nWhy you must use a LEFT JOIN here\nYour goal is to see all students. If you use a LEFT JOIN, you are telling the database: \"Give me every single row from the Students table. If you find their ID in the Clubs table, attach the club name. If you don\'t find them, just leave the club name blank, but make sure the student stays on the list.\"\n\nThe Query:\n\nSQL\nSELECT Students.student_name, Clubs.club_name\nFROM Students\nLEFT JOIN Clubs ON Students.student_id = Clubs.student_id;\nThe Result:\n| student_name | club_name |\n| :--- | :--- |\n| Alice | Drama Club |\n| Bob | Chess Team |\n| Charlie | NULL |\n| Diana | Debate Society |\n\nThanks to the LEFT JOIN, Charlie is still on your roster. You now accurately know that he is a student at the school who currently lacks an extracurricular activity.', 'MySQL', 90, '[\"clearly explained the difference between LEFT JOIN and INNER JOIN\", \"provided a relevant scenario to illustrate the use of LEFT JOIN\", \"included a concrete example with tables and a query\"]', '[\"could have mentioned other scenarios where LEFT JOIN is useful\", \"did not discuss potential performance implications of using LEFT JOIN\", \"did not provide alternative solutions or variations on the query\"]', '[\"study other types of JOINs, such as FULL OUTER JOIN, to be more versatile in database querying\", \"practice optimizing queries for performance, especially when working with large datasets\", \"review iOS-specific database integration, such as using Core Data or SQLite, to be more familiar with the technologies used in the role\"]'),
(558, 61, 'How would you approach creating a simple bar chart using a data visualization library, and what factors would you consider when choosing a library?', 'To create a bar chart, first structure your data as an array of categories and values.\nNext, define an HTML container like a <canvas> or <svg> to hold the visualization.\nMap your data values to visual pixels using mathematical scales for the X and Y axes.\nChoose a high-level library like Chart.js for rapid, out-of-the-box development.\nOpt for a low-level library like D3.js when you need absolute, pixel-perfect custom control.', 'Data Visualization', 80, '[\"identifies key steps in creating a bar chart\", \"recognizes importance of data structure\", \"distinguishes between high-level and low-level libraries\"]', '[\"lacks specificity in choosing a library for iOS development\", \"does not mention integration with iOS frameworks\", \"does not discuss performance or optimization considerations\"]', '[\"research and explore iOS-specific data visualization libraries like Core Plot or Swift Charts\", \"consider how to optimize chart performance for mobile devices with limited resources\", \"investigate how to integrate data visualization libraries with iOS frameworks like UIKit or SwiftUI\"]'),
(559, 61, 'What are some common pitfalls to avoid when creating a bar chart, and how would you ensure that your chart is readable and effective?', 'Always start your Y-axis at zero to prevent visual distortion of the data\'s true proportions.\nSort your bars by value rather than randomly to instantly highlight rankings and trends.\nSwitch to a horizontal format if your category labels are too long or overlap.\nAvoid 3D effects or heavy gridlines, keeping the design clean and focused strictly on the data.', 'Data Visualization', 85, '[\"identifies the importance of starting the Y-axis at zero\", \"recognizes the value of sorting bars to highlight rankings and trends\", \"considers the impact of category label length on chart format\", \"emphasizes the need for a clean design\"]', '[\"could provide more specific examples or scenarios where these pitfalls are common\", \"might benefit from discussing the role of color and contrast in readability\", \"could delve deeper into how to handle negative values or zero values in bar charts\"]', '[\"study the work of data visualization experts like Edward Tufte for inspiration on effective design\", \"practice creating bar charts with varying data sets to develop an intuition for what works well\", \"consider exploring libraries like Charts or Plot that can help streamline the creation of readable and effective charts in iOS applications\"]'),
(560, 61, 'What is the purpose of unit testing in software development, and how do you write effective unit tests for a Swift application?', 'Gemini said\nUnit testing ensures individual code components work correctly in isolation, acting as a safety net against future bugs.\nIn Swift, you use the XCTest framework by creating test classes that inherit from XCTestCase.\nWrite effective tests using the Arrange, Act, Assert pattern: set up data, execute the function, and verify the result.\nKeep your tests fast, deterministic, and heavily reliant on XCTAssert macros to strictly validate expected outcomes.', 'Unit Testing', 90, '[\"clear understanding of unit testing purpose\", \"knowledge of XCTest framework\", \"familiarity with Arrange, Act, Assert pattern\"]', '[\"could provide more details on test-driven development\", \"limited discussion on mocking and stubbing\", \"no mention of testing for edge cases\"]', '[\"study test-driven development to improve code quality\", \"learn about mocking and stubbing to isolate dependencies\", \"practice writing tests for edge cases and error scenarios in Swift applications\"]'),
(561, 61, 'Can you explain how you would use a testing framework like XCTest to write and run unit tests for a Swift application?', 'To use XCTest, first import the framework and create a test class inheriting from XCTestCase.\nDefine your individual test methods, ensuring each function name starts with the word test.\nFollow the Arrange-Act-Assert pattern: set up your data, execute the target Swift code, and verify the output.\nUse macros like XCTAssertEqual or XCTAssertNotNil to strictly validate that the results match your expectations.\nFinally, run your test suite directly in Xcode by pressing Cmd + U or clicking the diamond icons in the gutter.', 'Unit Testing', 90, '[\"Correctly identified the testing framework XCTest\", \"Mentioned the importance of the Arrange-Act-Assert pattern\", \"Knew how to run the test suite in Xcode\"]', '[\"Could have provided more details about test-driven development\", \"Did not mention how to handle asynchronous testing\", \"Did not discuss how to use mocking or stubbing in tests\"]', '[\"Study how to use XCTest to test asynchronous code with expectations\", \"Learn about mocking and stubbing libraries like Mockingbird or SwiftMock\", \"Practice writing unit tests using the Arrange-Act-Assert pattern for different Swift applications\"]'),
(562, 61, 'What is a REST API, and how do you make a GET request to a REST API using Swift?', 'A REST API is a standard architectural style that allows applications to communicate over the web using HTTP methods like GET, POST, or DELETE.\nIn Swift, you typically make a GET request by utilizing the built-in URLSession API to fetch data asynchronously.\nFirst, safely construct a URL object from your endpoint string and use it to create a URLSession.shared.dataTask.\nInside the task\'s completion handler, check for network errors, verify the HTTP response code, and safely unwrap the returned Data.', 'REST API', 80, '[\"Identified REST API as an architectural style for web communication\", \"Mentioned HTTP methods like GET, POST, or DELETE\", \"Described using URLSession API in Swift for making a GET request\"]', '[\"Lacked detailed explanation of REST API principles\", \"Did not provide example code for making a GET request in Swift\", \"Did not discuss error handling in depth\"]', '[\"Study REST API principles such as resource-based architecture and statelessness\", \"Practice writing Swift code for making HTTP requests using URLSession\", \"Review Apple\'s documentation on URLSession and URLLoading system for more information on error handling and best practices\"]'),
(563, 61, 'How do you handle errors and exceptions when making a request to a REST API, and what are some common status codes that you might encounter?', 'Handle errors by first checking the error object returned by your network task for connectivity issues.\nNext, cast the response to an HTTPURLResponse to verify the status code falls within the successful 200-299 range.\nWrap your data parsing logic in a do-catch block to safely catch and handle DecodingError exceptions.\nCommon client error status codes you will encounter include 400 (Bad Request), 401 (Unauthorized), and 404 (Not Found).\nCommon server error status codes include 500 (Internal Server Error) and 503 (Service Unavailable).', 'REST API', 80, '[\"Identified key error handling steps\", \"Recognized importance of status codes\", \"Mentioned specific common status codes\"]', '[\"Lack of detail in error handling mechanisms\", \"No mention of retry mechanisms or logging\", \"Limited discussion of server error handling\"]', '[\"Implement retry logic for transient network errors\", \"Log error details for debugging and analytics purposes\", \"Handle server errors with user-friendly messages and potential fallbacks\", \"Consider using a networking library like Alamofire for streamlined error handling\", \"Review Apple\'s documentation on URLLoadingSystem for best practices on error handling in iOS applications\"]'),
(564, 61, 'What is the difference between the MVC and MVVM architectural patterns, and when would you use each in a Swift application?', 'MVC tightly couples the View and Controller, often leading to massive, hard-to-test ViewControllers in standard iOS development.\nMVVM introduces a ViewModel to handle all presentation logic, leaving the View purely responsible for rendering the UI.\nUse MVC for very small, simple applications or quick prototypes where complex architectural overhead isn\'t justified.\nUse MVVM for robust, data-driven apps to improve testability and cleanly implement reactive bindings, especially in SwiftUI.', 'MVVM', 90, '[\"Correctly identifies the tight coupling issue in MVC\", \"Accurately describes the role of the ViewModel in MVVM\", \"Provides a reasonable guideline for choosing between MVC and MVVM\"]', '[\"Could provide more details about the benefits of MVVM, such as two-way data binding and command patterns\", \"Does not explicitly mention the role of the Model in both patterns\", \"Does not discuss potential drawbacks of MVVM, such as increased complexity\"]', '[\"Study the specific implementation details of MVVM in SwiftUI, such as the use of @Published and @ObservedObject\", \"Practice implementing both MVC and MVVM in sample projects to develop a deeper understanding of their trade-offs\", \"Review the official Apple documentation and Swift community resources to stay up-to-date with best practices for iOS application architecture\"]'),
(565, 61, 'Can you explain how you would implement data binding in an MVVM application, and what benefits does it provide over a traditional MVC approach?', 'Implement data binding using Combine\'s @Published properties or simple closure-based observables within your ViewModel.\nThe View subscribes to these properties, automatically updating its UI elements the moment the underlying data changes.\nUnlike MVC, this completely decouples your architecture, as the ViewModel never needs to reference the View directly.\nThis eliminates tedious manual UI updates, drastically reducing boilerplate code and preventing out-of-sync state bugs.', 'MVVM', 90, '[\"clearly explained data binding implementation using Combine\'s @Published properties\", \"identified the benefits of MVVM over MVC\", \"recognized the decoupling of architecture as a key advantage\"]', '[\"could have provided more specific examples or code snippets to illustrate the implementation\", \"did not explicitly mention the role of the View Model in exposing the data\", \"might have elaborated on error handling and edge cases in data binding\"]', '[\"study the latest developments in Combine and Swift UI to stay up-to-date with best practices in MVVM data binding\", \"practice implementing MVVM in personal projects to solidify understanding of the pattern\", \"review Apple\'s documentation on MVVM and data binding to ensure a thorough grasp of the underlying frameworks and technologies\"]'),
(566, 62, 'How would you optimize the performance of a SQL query that is retrieving a large amount of data from an Oracle database, and what indexing strategies would you use?', 'No answer provided.', 'SQL Querying', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Provide a basic understanding of SQL query optimization\", \"Explain indexing strategies for Oracle databases\", \"Discuss the importance of efficient data retrieval for data science tasks\"]', '[\"Research and understand the fundamentals of SQL query optimization\", \"Familiarize yourself with Oracle database indexing strategies, such as B-tree and bitmap indexing\", \"Practice optimizing SQL queries for large datasets to improve data retrieval efficiency as a data scientist\"]'),
(567, 62, 'Can you explain how you would monitor the performance of the query and what tools you would use to identify bottlenecks?', 'No answer provided.', 'SQL Querying', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Provide a clear and concise explanation of query performance monitoring\", \"Familiarize themselves with industry-standard tools for bottleneck identification\", \"Demonstrate understanding of database optimization techniques\"]', '[\"Study SQL query optimization techniques\", \"Familiarize themselves with tools like EXPLAIN, EXPLAIN ANALYZE, and pg_stat_statements\", \"Practice monitoring query performance using database administration tools\"]'),
(568, 62, 'Given a dataset with missing values, how would you handle the missing data using data analysis techniques, and what methods would you use to impute the missing values?', 'No answer provided.', 'Data Analysis', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Provide a clear and concise answer to the question\", \"Demonstrate knowledge of data analysis techniques for handling missing values\", \"Explain methods for imputing missing values\"]', '[\"Familiarize yourself with industry-standard methods for handling missing data, such as mean/median/mode imputation, regression imputation, and K-Nearest Neighbors imputation\", \"Review data analysis techniques, including data cleaning, feature scaling, and data transformation\", \"Practice explaining complex technical concepts in a clear and concise manner, tailored to a Data Scientist role\"]'),
(569, 62, 'Can you describe a situation where you would use a specific imputation method, such as mean or median imputation, and why you would choose that method over others?', 'No answer provided.', 'Data Analysis', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Provide a clear understanding of imputation methods\", \"Explain the context in which a specific imputation method is chosen\", \"Demonstrate knowledge of the advantages and disadvantages of different imputation techniques\"]', '[\"Review the different types of imputation methods, such as mean, median, and imputation using regression\", \"Practice explaining the reasoning behind choosing a specific imputation method for a given scenario\", \"Consider discussing the importance of understanding the data distribution and the potential impact of imputation on model performance\"]'),
(570, 62, 'How would you design a data visualization dashboard using a Java-based tool, such as JFreeChart or XChart, to display complex data insights to a non-technical audience?', 'No answer provided.', 'Data Visualization', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Provide a basic understanding of data visualization principles\", \"Familiarize themselves with Java-based data visualization tools such as JFreeChart or XChart\", \"Develop skills to explain technical concepts to non-technical audiences\"]', '[\"Research and review documentation for JFreeChart or XChart to understand their capabilities and limitations\", \"Practice designing sample dashboards using Java-based tools to improve their skills\", \"Focus on learning how to effectively communicate complex data insights to non-technical stakeholders\"]'),
(571, 62, 'Can you walk me through your process for selecting the most appropriate visualization type, such as a bar chart or scatter plot, for a given dataset and audience?', 'No answer provided.', 'Data Visualization', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Provide a clear and concise answer to the question\", \"Demonstrate knowledge of different visualization types and their use cases\", \"Show understanding of the importance of considering the audience and dataset when selecting a visualization\"]', '[\"Review common data visualization types and their applications\", \"Practice explaining technical concepts to non-technical audiences\", \"Prepare examples of how to choose appropriate visualizations for different datasets and stakeholders\"]');
INSERT INTO `question_answers` (`id`, `interview_id`, `question`, `answer`, `category`, `score`, `strengths`, `improvements`, `suggestions`) VALUES
(572, 62, 'Can you explain the concept of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) in computer vision, and how they are used for image classification tasks?', 'No answer provided.', 'Computer Vision', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Provide a basic definition of convolutional neural networks\", \"Explain the role of convolutional and pooling layers in CNNs\", \"Describe the application of CNNs in image classification tasks\"]', '[\"Review the fundamental concepts of computer vision and deep learning\", \"Familiarize yourself with popular CNN architectures such as LeNet, AlexNet, and ResNet\", \"Practice explaining technical concepts in a clear and concise manner to improve communication skills\"]'),
(573, 62, 'How would you implement a CNN using a programming language like C++, and what considerations would you take into account when selecting a deep learning framework?', 'No answer provided.', 'Computer Vision', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Provide a basic understanding of CNN implementation\", \"Discuss considerations for selecting a deep learning framework\", \"Familiarity with C++ and deep learning frameworks\"]', '[\"Research and review the basics of CNN architecture and implementation\", \"Investigate popular deep learning frameworks such as TensorFlow or PyTorch and their C++ APIs\", \"Practice implementing simple CNN models using C++ and a chosen framework to gain hands-on experience\"]'),
(574, 62, 'How would you design a database schema to store and manage large amounts of data in an Oracle database, and what considerations would you take into account when selecting data types and indexing strategies?', 'No answer provided.', 'Oracle', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Provide a basic understanding of database schema design\", \"Explain considerations for selecting data types\", \"Discuss indexing strategies for large datasets\"]', '[\"Familiarize yourself with Oracle database architecture and data types\", \"Research best practices for database schema design and indexing\", \"Practice designing and implementing database schemas for large datasets as a Data Scientist\"]'),
(575, 62, 'Can you describe a situation where you would use a specific database design pattern, such as star or snowflake schema, and why you would choose that pattern over others?', 'No answer provided.', 'Oracle', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Provide a basic understanding of database design patterns\", \"Familiarize with star and snowflake schema\", \"Develop ability to apply database design patterns to real-world scenarios\"]', '[\"Study database design patterns and their applications\", \"Practice designing databases for various use cases\", \"Review data warehousing concepts and ETL processes relevant to data science role\"]'),
(576, 63, 'What is the difference between var, let, and constant in Swift?', 'xqwx', 'Swift', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Lack of understanding of Swift basics\", \"Failure to provide a relevant answer\"]', '[\"Review the Swift documentation on variable declarations\", \"Practice explaining the difference between var, let, and constant in Swift\", \"Focus on providing clear and concise answers to technical questions\"]'),
(577, 63, 'Can you provide an example of when you would use each?', 'xqsxq', 'Swift', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Lack of understanding of the question\", \"Failure to provide a relevant example\", \"Inability to communicate technical concepts effectively\"]', '[\"Review the fundamentals of Swift programming language\", \"Practice explaining technical concepts in a clear and concise manner\", \"Prepare examples of common iOS development scenarios to demonstrate problem-solving skills\"]'),
(578, 63, 'How do you handle errors in PHP?', 'saxasxa', 'PHP', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Lack of relevant knowledge in PHP\", \"Failure to provide a coherent answer\", \"Inability to demonstrate error handling skills\"]', '[\"Study PHP error handling mechanisms, such as try-catch blocks and error types\", \"Review industry standards for error handling in PHP, such as logging and error reporting\", \"Prepare to answer technical questions relevant to the iOS Application Developer role, focusing on Swift or Objective-C error handling instead of PHP\"]'),
(579, 63, 'What is the difference between try-catch and error handling using if-else statements?', 'xz', 'PHP', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Lack of relevant knowledge in PHP\", \"Failure to address the question\", \"No indication of understanding error handling concepts\"]', '[\"Study PHP basics, including error handling mechanisms\", \"Review differences between try-catch blocks and if-else statements for error handling\", \"Prepare to answer technical questions relevant to the iOS Application Developer role, focusing on Swift or Objective-C rather than PHP\"]'),
(580, 63, 'What is the purpose of Git in the development process?', 'sc cs', 'Git', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Lack of understanding of Git basics\", \"Inability to articulate the purpose of Git\", \"Unrelated response to the question\"]', '[\"Study the fundamentals of Git and its role in version control\", \"Review how Git is used in the iOS development process\", \"Prepare to provide clear and concise answers to technical questions related to Git and iOS development\"]'),
(581, 63, 'Can you explain the difference between Git fetch and Git pull?', 'sdsd sd', 'Git', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Provide a clear and concise answer\", \"Understand the basics of Git commands\", \"Familiarize yourself with Git workflow\"]', '[\"Review the official Git documentation to understand the difference between Git fetch and Git pull\", \"Practice using Git commands in a real-world project to gain hands-on experience\", \"Focus on learning the fundamentals of Git as it is a crucial tool for any iOS Application Developer\"]'),
(582, 63, 'How do you structure a REST API endpoint?', 'ds sd', 'REST API', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Lack of understanding of REST API endpoint structure\", \"Failure to provide a coherent answer\"]', '[\"Study the basic principles of REST API design\", \"Review HTTP request methods and their uses\", \"Practice designing and implementing REST API endpoints in iOS applications\"]'),
(583, 63, 'What HTTP methods would you use for creating, reading, updating, and deleting resources?', 'ds sd', 'REST API', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Lack of understanding of HTTP methods\", \"Inability to provide a clear and concise answer\", \"Failure to demonstrate knowledge of REST API fundamentals\"]', '[\"Study the basics of REST API and HTTP methods such as POST, GET, PUT/PATCH, and DELETE\", \"Review the role of each HTTP method in CRUD operations\", \"Practice explaining technical concepts clearly and concisely to improve communication skills\"]'),
(584, 63, 'How do you send and receive data in JSON format using Swift?', 'd sd s', 'JSON', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Lack of relevant technical knowledge\", \"Inability to provide a clear and concise answer\", \"Failure to demonstrate understanding of JSON and Swift\"]', '[\"Review Swift documentation for JSON encoding and decoding\", \"Familiarize yourself with URLSession and Codable protocols\", \"Practice implementing JSON data transfer in a Swift-based iOS application\"]'),
(585, 63, 'What is the difference between JSONSerialization and Codable?', 'ds  sd', 'JSON', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Provide a clear and concise answer\", \"Demonstrate knowledge of JSONSerialization and Codable\", \"Explain the difference between the two\"]', '[\"Study the differences between JSONSerialization and Codable in Swift\", \"Practice explaining technical concepts in a clear and concise manner\", \"Review the official Apple documentation for JSONSerialization and Codable to better understand their usage in iOS development\"]'),
(586, 64, 'How do you handle errors in Swift, and what are some best practices for error handling in a SwiftUI application?', 'error handle use auto generation and verfiy the data', 'Swift', 10, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Lack of understanding of error handling mechanisms in Swift\", \"Insufficient knowledge of best practices for error handling in SwiftUI\", \"Poor communication skills\"]', '[\"Study Swift\'s error handling mechanisms, such as try-catch blocks and error types\", \"Learn about SwiftUI\'s built-in error handling features, such as the .error modifier\", \"Practice explaining technical concepts clearly and concisely\", \"Review Apple\'s documentation on error handling in Swift and SwiftUI\", \"Implement error handling in a sample SwiftUI project to gain hands-on experience\"]'),
(587, 64, 'Can you give an example of how you would use a try-catch block to handle a specific error in a SwiftUI view model?', 'mvvm', 'Swift', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Lack of understanding of try-catch blocks in Swift\", \"Failure to provide a relevant example\", \"Insufficient knowledge of SwiftUI view models\"]', '[\"Study the basics of error handling in Swift, including try-catch blocks and error types\", \"Review the architecture of SwiftUI view models and their role in handling errors\", \"Practice implementing try-catch blocks in SwiftUI view models to handle specific errors, such as networking or data parsing errors\"]'),
(588, 64, 'What is the purpose of Git, and how do you use it for version control in a team environment?', 'no', 'Git', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Lack of understanding of Git and its purpose\", \"Inability to explain version control in a team environment\"]', '[\"Study the basics of Git and its application in version control\", \"Learn how to initialize and manage Git repositories\", \"Understand how to collaborate with team members using Git\", \" Familiarize yourself with Git commands and best practices for iOS development teams\"]'),
(589, 64, 'How do you resolve conflicts that arise when merging branches in Git, and what strategies do you use to avoid conflicts in the first place?', 'it;fig', 'Git', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Provide a clear and concise answer\", \"Demonstrate understanding of Git conflict resolution\", \"Explain strategies for avoiding conflicts\"]', '[\"Study Git documentation and practice resolving conflicts\", \"Learn about Git merge strategies and tools like git merge --abort or git merge --continue\", \"Understand how to use git diff and git status to identify and resolve conflicts in iOS development projects\"]'),
(590, 64, 'What are some key principles of Data Visualization, and how do you apply them when creating visualizations for a mobile application?', 'vd', 'Data Visualization', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Lack of understanding of data visualization principles\", \"Inability to provide relevant examples\", \"Failure to demonstrate knowledge of mobile application development\"]', '[\"Study key principles of data visualization such as clarity, accuracy, and aesthetics\", \"Research how to apply these principles in a mobile application context\", \"Practice creating visualizations for mobile applications using tools like Swift UI or third-party libraries\", \"Review industry standards for data visualization in mobile applications, such as those provided by Apple or Google\"]'),
(591, 64, 'How do you choose the most effective chart type for a given dataset, and what considerations do you take into account when designing a visualization for a small screen?', 'v', 'Data Visualization', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Lack of understanding of data visualization principles\", \"Inability to articulate considerations for small screen design\", \"Failure to provide examples of effective chart types\"]', '[\"Study data visualization best practices, such as those outlined by Edward Tufte or Stephen Few\", \"Research iOS-specific design guidelines for small screens, including Apple\'s Human Interface Guidelines\", \"Practice designing and implementing different chart types, such as bar charts, line charts, and scatter plots, using iOS frameworks like UIKit or third-party libraries like Charts or Plot\"]'),
(592, 64, 'What is a REST API, and how do you use it to interact with a backend service from a mobile application?', 'fvevfev', 'REST API', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Provide a clear and concise definition of REST API\", \"Explain the basic principles of REST API\", \"Describe how to use REST API in a mobile application\"]', '[\"Study the fundamentals of REST API and its application in mobile development\", \"Review iOS networking frameworks such as URLSession or third-party libraries like Alamofire\", \"Practice implementing REST API calls in a mobile application using Swift or other relevant programming languages\"]'),
(593, 64, 'Can you describe how you would handle authentication and authorization when making requests to a REST API from a mobile app?', 'verfd', 'REST API', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Provide a clear and concise answer\", \"Demonstrate knowledge of authentication and authorization concepts\", \"Explain how to handle authentication and authorization in a mobile app\"]', '[\"Study REST API security best practices\", \"Research OAuth, JWT, and other authentication protocols\", \"Learn how to implement secure authentication and authorization in an iOS application using Swift or Objective-C\"]'),
(594, 64, 'How do you approach testing a new feature in a mobile application, and what types of tests do you typically write?', 'berbebt', 'Unit Testing', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Provide a clear and concise answer\", \"Explain the approach to testing a new feature\", \"Mention types of tests typically written\"]', '[\"Study the different types of tests such as unit tests, integration tests, and UI tests\", \"Learn about testing frameworks like XCTest and how to write test cases\", \"Practice writing tests for a mobile application to improve understanding of testing concepts\"]'),
(595, 64, 'Can you give an example of how you would write a unit test for a specific piece of functionality in a SwiftUI view model using XCTest?', 'vbrebtrebtr', 'Unit Testing', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Provide a relevant and accurate code example\", \"Demonstrate understanding of XCTest and unit testing principles\", \"Show familiarity with SwiftUI view models\"]', '[\"Review Apple\'s official documentation on XCTest and unit testing in SwiftUI\", \"Practice writing unit tests for view models using XCTest\", \"Familiarize yourself with SwiftUI view model architecture and best practices\"]'),
(596, 65, 'What is the purpose of the @SpringBootApplication annotation in a Spring Boot application?', 'dewdw', 'Spring Boot', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Lack of understanding of Spring Boot annotations\", \"Failure to provide a relevant answer\", \"No demonstration of knowledge in the area\"]', '[\"Review the purpose and usage of @SpringBootApplication annotation\", \"Study the role of annotations in Spring Boot applications\", \"Prepare to provide clear and concise answers to technical questions related to the position of Software Developer\"]'),
(597, 65, 'Can you explain how it enables auto-configuration?', 'sdsq', 'Spring Boot', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Lack of understanding of Spring Boot auto-configuration\", \"Inability to provide a clear and concise answer\", \"Failure to demonstrate relevant technical knowledge\"]', '[\"Study the Spring Boot documentation to understand how auto-configuration works\", \"Practice explaining technical concepts in a clear and concise manner\", \"Review the basics of Spring Boot and its features to improve technical knowledge\"]'),
(598, 65, 'How do you create a simple Python function to print \'Hello World\'?', 'saxasx', 'Python', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Understanding of basic Python syntax\", \"Ability to write simple functions\", \"Familiarity with standard output in Python\"]', '[\"Review the basics of Python programming\", \"Practice writing simple functions with clear and descriptive names\", \"Learn how to use the print function in Python to output strings to the console\"]'),
(599, 65, 'What is the purpose of the print() function in Python?', 'xasxa', 'Python', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Lack of understanding of basic Python functions\", \"Failure to provide a relevant answer\"]', '[\"Review the basics of Python programming\", \"Familiarize yourself with the print() function and its usage in Python\", \"Practice providing clear and concise answers to technical questions\"]'),
(600, 65, 'What is the difference between \'==\' and \'.equals()\' in Java?', 'saxsa', 'Java', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Lack of understanding of basic Java concepts\", \"Inability to provide a clear and concise answer\", \"Failure to address the question directly\"]', '[\"Review the basics of Java, including operators and methods\", \"Practice explaining technical concepts in a clear and concise manner\", \"Familiarize yourself with common Java interview questions and practice responding to them accurately\"]'),
(601, 65, 'Can you provide an example where using \'==\' would be incorrect?', 'asxa', 'Java', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Provide a clear and relevant example\", \"Demonstrate understanding of Java syntax and operators\", \"Communicate effectively and avoid using nonsensical words\"]', '[\"Review Java documentation on equality operators\", \"Practice explaining technical concepts in a clear and concise manner\", \"Prepare examples of common Java pitfalls, such as using \'==\' for object comparison instead of equals() method\"]'),
(602, 65, 'What is the basic structure of an HTML document?', 'xaxa', 'HTML', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Lack of understanding of HTML basics\", \"Failure to provide a relevant answer\"]', '[\"Review the basic structure of an HTML document, including doctype, html, head, and body tags\", \"Familiarize yourself with standard HTML elements and their uses\", \"Practice explaining technical concepts clearly and concisely\"]'),
(603, 65, 'What is the purpose of the <head> tag in HTML?', 'saxas', 'HTML', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Lack of understanding of basic HTML tags\", \"Failure to provide a relevant answer\"]', '[\"Review the basics of HTML structure and tags\", \"Familiarize yourself with the purpose and usage of the <head> tag in HTML documents\", \"Practice providing clear and concise answers to technical questions\"]'),
(604, 65, 'What is the purpose of the \'style\' attribute in CSS?', 'xsaxasxsaxasx', 'CSS', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Provide a clear and concise answer\", \"Understand the basics of CSS\", \"Familiarize with standard CSS attributes\"]', '[\"Review the CSS specification to understand the purpose of the \'style\' attribute\", \"Practice explaining technical concepts in a clear and concise manner\", \"Focus on learning the fundamentals of CSS and its applications in web development\"]'),
(605, 65, 'Can you provide an example of how to use it to change the color of a paragraph?', 'xs zx', 'CSS', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Provide a relevant and accurate answer\", \"Demonstrate understanding of CSS basics\", \"Use proper terminology and syntax\"]', '[\"Review CSS documentation for text color property\", \"Practice writing simple CSS selectors and properties\", \"Familiarize yourself with standard CSS syntax and examples\"]'),
(606, 66, 'Can you walk me through a complex problem you solved using Data Visualization?', 'No answer provided.', 'Data Visualization', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Lack of relevant experience\", \"Inability to communicate problem-solving skills\", \"Failure to provide a meaningful example\"]', '[\"Prepare examples of complex problems solved using data visualization prior to the interview\", \"Familiarize yourself with common data visualization tools and techniques\", \"Practice articulating technical experiences and skills clearly and concisely\"]'),
(607, 66, 'How do you stay updated with the latest developments in Data Visualization?', 'No answer provided.', 'Data Visualization', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Lack of response to the question\", \"Failure to demonstrate knowledge of data visualization trends and updates\", \"Inability to articulate personal efforts to stay current in the field\"]', '[\"Research industry leaders and blogs in data visualization to stay updated\", \"Participate in online forums and discussions related to data visualization\", \"Pursue certifications or courses to enhance knowledge and skills in data visualization\", \"Develop a personal project or contribute to open-source projects to demonstrate expertise and interest in data visualization\"]'),
(608, 66, 'How do you stay updated with the latest developments in SQL Querying?', 'No answer provided.', 'SQL Querying', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Lack of response to the question\", \"Unable to demonstrate knowledge of SQL querying developments\", \"Missed opportunity to showcase enthusiasm for learning and professional growth\"]', '[\"Research industry publications and websites, such as SQL Server Magazine or Database Trends and Applications\", \"Participate in online forums and discussion groups, like Reddit\'s r/learnsql or r/sql\", \"Attend webinars, conferences, or workshops on SQL querying and data analysis\", \"Join online courses or certification programs to enhance SQL skills and knowledge\", \"Network with professionals in the field to stay informed about best practices and new developments\"]'),
(609, 66, 'Describe a Java project you worked on and the design patterns you applied.', 'No answer provided.', 'Java', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Provide a clear and concise description of a Java project\", \"Explain the design patterns applied in the project\", \"Demonstrate knowledge of Java and its applications in data analysis\"]', '[\"Review Java fundamentals and design patterns\", \"Prepare examples of personal projects or experiences working with Java\", \"Familiarize yourself with industry-standard data analysis tools and technologies in Java\"]'),
(610, 66, 'How do you manage memory and performance in a Java application?', 'No answer provided.', 'Java', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Lack of knowledge in Java memory management\", \"Unable to discuss performance optimization techniques\", \"Inability to provide relevant examples or experiences\"]', '[\"Study Java memory management concepts, such as garbage collection and heap sizing\", \"Research performance optimization techniques, including caching, indexing, and query optimization\", \"Prepare to discuss how to use Java profiling tools, such as VisualVM or JProfiler, to identify performance bottlenecks\", \"Review how to apply data structures and algorithms to improve application performance as a Data Analyst\"]'),
(611, 66, 'Explain memory management in C++ and how you avoid common pitfalls.', 'No answer provided.', 'C++', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Lack of knowledge in C++ memory management\", \"Inability to identify common pitfalls\", \"Failure to provide any relevant information\"]', '[\"Study the basics of C++ memory management, including pointers, references, and smart pointers\", \"Review common pitfalls such as dangling pointers, memory leaks, and wild pointers\", \"Practice explaining technical concepts in a clear and concise manner\", \"Familiarize yourself with data structures and algorithms relevant to data analysis\"]'),
(612, 66, 'How do you handle multi-threading safely in C++?', 'No answer provided.', 'C++', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Lack of knowledge in C++ multi-threading\", \"Inability to provide a relevant example or explanation\", \"Failure to demonstrate understanding of data analysis role requirements\"]', '[\"Study C++11 threading library and its usage\", \"Review synchronization primitives such as mutexes and locks\", \"Research how multi-threading applies to data analysis tasks and workflows\"]'),
(613, 66, 'Explain your experience with Python and describe the projects you built with it.', 'No answer provided.', 'Python', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Lack of experience sharing\", \"No project descriptions provided\", \"Failure to demonstrate Python skills\"]', '[\"Prepare to discuss Python projects and experiences before the interview\", \"Review common Python data analysis libraries such as Pandas and NumPy\", \"Practice explaining technical details of projects to improve communication skills\"]'),
(614, 66, 'Which Python frameworks or libraries have you used, and what were your reasons for choosing them?', 'No answer provided.', 'Python', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Lack of experience with Python frameworks or libraries\", \"Inability to articulate reasons for choosing specific frameworks or libraries\"]', '[\"Familiarize yourself with popular Python data analysis libraries such as Pandas, NumPy, and Matplotlib\", \"Research and understand the use cases for different Python frameworks such as Flask or Django\", \"Prepare to discuss your experience and decision-making process when selecting specific libraries or frameworks for a project\"]'),
(615, 66, 'How would you explain the core concepts of SQL to a junior engineer?', 'No answer provided.', 'SQL', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Provide a clear and concise explanation of SQL core concepts\", \"Demonstrate understanding of SQL fundamentals\", \"Show ability to communicate technical information to junior engineers\"]', '[\"Review SQL basics, including SELECT, FROM, WHERE, GROUP BY, and JOIN clauses\", \"Prepare examples to illustrate SQL concepts, such as data retrieval and manipulation\", \"Practice explaining technical information in a clear and concise manner, tailored to a junior engineer audience\"]'),
(616, 67, 'What is the difference between SwiftUI and UIKit, and when would you use each?', 'sasad', 'SwiftUI', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Lack of understanding of SwiftUI and UIKit\", \"Failure to provide a clear and concise answer\", \"No relevant examples or use cases provided\"]', '[\"Study the official Apple documentation on SwiftUI and UIKit to understand their differences and use cases\", \"Practice explaining technical concepts in a clear and concise manner\", \"Review common iOS development scenarios to determine when to use SwiftUI versus UIKit\"]'),
(617, 67, 'Can you give an example of a simple app that would be better suited for SwiftUI versus UIKit?', 'jbkj', 'SwiftUI', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Provide a relevant example\", \"Demonstrate understanding of SwiftUI and UIKit\", \"Communicate effectively\"]', '[\"Study the differences between SwiftUI and UIKit\", \"Practice explaining technical concepts clearly\", \"Review common use cases for SwiftUI, such as simple data-driven apps or prototyping tools\"]'),
(618, 67, 'How do you handle errors and debugging in Xcode, especially when working with Core Data?', 'mm,nlkl', 'Xcode', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Provide a clear and concise answer\", \"Demonstrate knowledge of Xcode error handling and debugging tools\", \"Show understanding of Core Data and its error handling mechanisms\"]', '[\"Familiarize yourself with Xcode\'s built-in debugging tools such as the Debugger and Console\", \"Learn about Core Data error types and how to handle them\", \"Practice using breakpoints and the Xcode Debugger to step through code and identify issues\"]'),
(619, 67, 'What tools or techniques do you use to identify and fix issues with your Core Data stack?', 'nll', 'Xcode', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Lack of knowledge about Core Data debugging tools\", \"Inability to identify and fix issues with Core Data stack\", \"Failure to provide any relevant techniques or tools\"]', '[\"Familiarize yourself with Xcode\'s built-in debugging tools for Core Data, such as the Core Data Debugger\", \"Learn about third-party libraries and tools, like Core Data Editor or Core Data Lab, to help identify and fix issues\", \"Review Apple\'s documentation on Core Data best practices and troubleshooting techniques to improve your skills and knowledge in this area\"]'),
(620, 67, 'What is Auto Layout, and how do you use it to create responsive UI designs in your iOS apps?', 'khlh', 'Auto Layout', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Lack of understanding of Auto Layout\", \"Inability to provide a clear and concise answer\", \"Failure to demonstrate knowledge of responsive UI design\"]', '[\"Study the fundamentals of Auto Layout and its application in iOS development\", \"Practice creating responsive UI designs using Auto Layout\", \"Review Apple\'s documentation and guidelines for using Auto Layout in iOS apps\"]'),
(621, 67, 'Can you explain how you would use Auto Layout to create a simple login screen with a username and password field?', ',jjkjjhbkj', 'Auto Layout', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Provide a clear and concise answer\", \"Demonstrate understanding of Auto Layout concepts\", \"Explain how to apply constraints to views\"]', '[\"Review Apple\'s documentation on Auto Layout\", \"Practice creating simple layouts using Auto Layout\", \"Focus on explaining the process of adding constraints to views, such as pinning edges or using stack views\"]'),
(622, 67, 'What is the purpose of TestFlight, and how do you use it to distribute and test your apps?', 'jbkjbjk', 'TestFlight', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Lack of understanding of TestFlight\", \"Inability to provide a clear answer\", \"Failure to demonstrate knowledge of iOS development tools\"]', '[\"Study the purpose and functionality of TestFlight\", \"Review the process of distributing and testing apps using TestFlight\", \" Familiarize yourself with Apple\'s documentation on TestFlight and iOS development best practices\"]'),
(623, 67, 'Can you walk me through the process of setting up TestFlight for a new app, including creating a beta version and inviting testers?', 'm,m', 'TestFlight', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Lack of understanding of TestFlight setup process\", \"Inability to articulate the steps involved in creating a beta version\", \"Failure to describe the process of inviting testers\"]', '[\"Review the official Apple documentation on TestFlight to understand the setup process\", \"Practice explaining the steps involved in creating a beta version and inviting testers\", \"Familiarize yourself with the iTunes Connect dashboard and the process of managing beta releases and tester invitations\"]'),
(624, 67, 'How do you implement a simple MVC pattern in a Swift iOS app, and what are the benefits of using this architecture?', 'jbbkbkj', 'MVC', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Provide a clear and concise definition of the MVC pattern\", \"Explain the roles of Model, View, and Controller in the architecture\", \"Discuss the benefits of using MVC in iOS app development\"]', '[\"Study the official Apple documentation on MVC pattern for iOS development\", \"Review Swift programming language basics and iOS development best practices\", \"Practice implementing MVC pattern in a simple iOS app project to gain hands-on experience\"]'),
(625, 67, 'Can you give an example of how you would use the MVC pattern to create a simple weather app that fetches data from a web API?', 'jkjblkblk', 'MVC', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Provide a clear and concise description of the MVC pattern\", \"Explain how to create a simple weather app that fetches data from a web API\", \"Include code examples or pseudocode to illustrate the implementation\"]', '[\"Review the Model-View-Controller pattern and its application in iOS development\", \"Study how to use APIs and networking in iOS to fetch data from a web API\", \"Practice creating a simple weather app using Swift or Objective-C and the MVC pattern to demonstrate understanding of the concept\"]'),
(626, 68, 'What is the difference between MVC and MVVM architecture patterns?', 'sdasdasd', 'MVC', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Provide a clear and concise definition of MVC and MVVM architecture patterns\", \"Explain the key differences between the two patterns\", \"Understand the role of each component in the patterns\"]', '[\"Study the Model-View-Controller (MVC) pattern and its components, including the model, view, and controller\", \"Research the Model-View-ViewModel (MVVM) pattern and its components, including the model, view, and view model\", \"Practice explaining the differences between MVC and MVVM in a clear and concise manner, tailored to iOS application development\"]'),
(627, 68, 'Can you provide an example of when you would use each pattern in a real-world application?', 'aa', 'MVC', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Lack of understanding of MVC pattern\", \"Inability to provide a real-world example\", \"Failure to demonstrate knowledge of iOS application development\"]', '[\"Study the Model-View-Controller pattern and its application in iOS development\", \"Review real-world examples of MVC implementation in iOS apps\", \"Practice explaining technical concepts clearly and concisely\"]'),
(628, 68, 'How do you optimize the performance of a MySQL database?', 'aa', 'MySQL', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Lack of understanding of MySQL performance optimization\", \"Failure to provide relevant technical details\", \"Inability to articulate a coherent response\"]', '[\"Study MySQL indexing and caching mechanisms\", \"Review query optimization techniques, such as EXPLAIN and ANALYZE\", \"Familiarize yourself with iOS backend technologies and database integration best practices\"]'),
(629, 68, 'What indexing strategies would you use to improve query performance?', 'AAA', 'MySQL', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Lack of understanding of indexing strategies\", \"Failure to provide relevant examples or techniques\", \"Insufficient knowledge of database performance optimization\"]', '[\"Study MySQL indexing strategies, such as B-Tree indexing and Hash indexing\", \"Familiarize yourself with query optimization techniques, including EXPLAIN and ANALYZE statements\", \"Review iOS application development best practices for integrating with MySQL databases, focusing on efficient data retrieval and storage\"]'),
(630, 68, 'How do you implement a simple recommendation system using collaborative filtering?', 'AA', 'Recommendation Systems', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Lack of understanding of collaborative filtering\", \"Failure to provide a basic algorithm or approach\", \"Insufficient knowledge of recommendation systems\"]', '[\"Study the basics of collaborative filtering and its types, such as user-based and item-based filtering\", \"Learn to implement a simple collaborative filtering algorithm using a library like Surprise or TensorFlow Recommenders\", \"Familiarize yourself with iOS-specific libraries or frameworks that can be used for building recommendation systems, such as Core ML or Apple\'s ML Kit\"]'),
(631, 68, 'How would you handle the cold start problem in a recommendation system?', 'AA', 'Recommendation Systems', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Lack of understanding of recommendation systems\", \"No clear approach to handling the cold start problem\", \"Failure to provide a meaningful answer\"]', '[\"Study the basics of recommendation systems and their challenges\", \"Research existing solutions to the cold start problem, such as content-based filtering or hybrid approaches\", \"Practice explaining technical concepts clearly and concisely, tailored to the iOS application development context\"]'),
(632, 68, 'What is the purpose of the REST API and how does it differ from other API protocols?', 'AAA', 'REST API', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Lack of understanding of REST API fundamentals\", \"Failure to provide a clear definition or purpose of REST API\", \"Inability to differentiate REST API from other API protocols\"]', '[\"Study the basic principles of REST API and its application in iOS development\", \"Familiarize yourself with other API protocols such as GraphQL and SOAP to understand the differences\", \"Practice explaining technical concepts in a clear and concise manner to improve communication skills\"]'),
(633, 68, 'Can you describe a scenario where you would use REST API to interact with a backend service?', 'AA', 'REST API', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Lack of understanding of REST API\", \"Inability to provide a relevant scenario\", \"Failure to demonstrate knowledge of backend service interaction\"]', '[\"Study the basics of REST API and its application in iOS development\", \"Practice describing scenarios where REST API is used to interact with backend services\", \"Review Apple\'s documentation on URL Loading and Networking to improve understanding of API integration in iOS apps\"]'),
(634, 68, 'How do you use GitHub Actions to automate the deployment of a Swift application?', 'ASAS', 'GitHub Actions', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Lack of understanding of GitHub Actions\", \"Failure to provide a relevant example\", \"Inability to apply automation concepts to Swift application deployment\"]', '[\"Research GitHub Actions documentation and its application in automating iOS development workflows\", \"Familiarize yourself with YAML files and workflow configuration\", \"Explore existing GitHub Actions for Swift and iOS projects to understand best practices and implementation details\"]'),
(635, 68, 'Can you explain how you would configure GitHub Actions to run unit tests and report test results?', 'SS', 'GitHub Actions', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Lack of understanding of GitHub Actions\", \"Inability to explain configuration for unit tests\", \"Failure to provide any relevant information\"]', '[\"Study GitHub Actions documentation to understand workflow files and syntax\", \"Research how to integrate unit tests with GitHub Actions for iOS projects\", \"Practice configuring GitHub Actions to run unit tests and report results for an iOS application\"]'),
(636, 69, 'How would you optimize the performance of a MySQL database for a high-traffic application, considering indexing, caching, and query optimization?', 'No answer provided.', 'MySQL', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Lack of knowledge in MySQL performance optimization\", \"Failure to provide any relevant information\", \"No understanding of indexing, caching, and query optimization\"]', '[\"Study MySQL performance optimization techniques\", \"Familiarize yourself with indexing strategies for high-traffic applications\", \"Learn about caching mechanisms, such as Redis or Memcached, to reduce database load\", \"Practice query optimization using EXPLAIN and ANALYZE statements\", \"Review iOS application development best practices for database integration\"]'),
(637, 69, 'Can you explain how you would implement indexing on a frequently queried column, and how it would impact the overall database performance?', 'No answer provided.', 'MySQL', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Lack of knowledge in database indexing\", \"Inability to explain database performance optimization\", \"Failure to provide any relevant information\"]', '[\"Study MySQL indexing and its application in iOS app development\", \"Learn to explain technical concepts in a clear and concise manner\", \"Prepare to answer database-related questions as they pertain to iOS application development\"]'),
(638, 69, 'Design a simple e-commerce application using the MVC pattern, and explain how you would handle user authentication and authorization', 'No answer provided.', 'MVC', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Provide a clear and concise design for a simple e-commerce application using the MVC pattern\", \"Explain how user authentication and authorization would be handled in the application\"]', '[\"Study the MVC pattern and its application in iOS development\", \"Research user authentication and authorization techniques, such as OAuth and JWT\", \"Practice designing and implementing simple e-commerce applications using the MVC pattern\", \"Review Apple\'s guidelines for iOS application development and security best practices\"]'),
(639, 69, 'How would you implement data binding and validation in the MVC pattern, and what are the benefits of using this approach?', 'No answer provided.', 'MVC', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Provide a clear understanding of the MVC pattern\", \"Explain data binding and validation implementation\", \"Discuss benefits of using the MVC approach\"]', '[\"Study the MVC pattern and its application in iOS development\", \"Review data binding and validation techniques in Swift or Objective-C\", \"Research industry-standard frameworks and libraries for MVC implementation in iOS\"]'),
(640, 69, 'Explain how you would implement a modular architecture in a Swift application, and discuss the benefits of using a modular approach', 'No answer provided.', 'Modular Architecture', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Provide a clear and concise explanation of modular architecture\", \"Discuss the benefits of a modular approach in Swift application development\", \"Explain how to implement modular architecture in a real-world scenario\"]', '[\"Research and understand the concept of modular architecture in software development\", \"Familiarize yourself with Swift programming language and its application in iOS development\", \"Review industry-standard design patterns and architectures for iOS applications, such as MVVM, VIPER, or Clean Architecture\"]'),
(641, 69, 'How would you handle dependency injection and module communication in a modular architecture, and what are the best practices for implementing this approach?', 'No answer provided.', 'Modular Architecture', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Provide a clear understanding of dependency injection and module communication\", \"Explain the best practices for implementing modular architecture\"]', '[\"Study the concepts of dependency injection and modular architecture\", \"Review industry-standard frameworks and libraries for iOS development, such as Swift Package Manager or CocoaPods\", \"Prepare to discuss design patterns and principles, such as Single Responsibility Principle and Separation of Concerns\"]'),
(642, 69, 'Design a REST API for a simple blog application, and explain how you would handle CRUD operations and error handling', 'No answer provided.', 'REST API', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Provide a basic design for a REST API\", \"Explain CRUD operations\", \"Describe error handling mechanisms\"]', '[\"Familiarize yourself with REST API principles and standards\", \"Review HTTP methods and their uses in CRUD operations\", \"Study error handling best practices for REST APIs, such as using HTTP status codes and error response bodies\"]'),
(643, 69, 'How would you implement authentication and authorization in the REST API, and what are the best practices for securing the API?', 'No answer provided.', 'REST API', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Provide a basic understanding of authentication and authorization concepts\", \"Explain common authentication protocols such as OAuth, JWT, or Basic Auth\", \"Discuss authorization techniques like role-based access control\"]', '[\"Study REST API security best practices and common authentication protocols\", \"Review Apple\'s guidelines for securing iOS applications and APIs\", \"Prepare to discuss implementation details of authentication and authorization in a real-world iOS application scenario\"]'),
(644, 69, 'Explain how you would implement data visualization in a SwiftUI application, and discuss the benefits of using data visualization in a mobile application', 'No answer provided.', 'Data Visualization', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Provide a clear and concise answer to the question\", \"Explain the implementation of data visualization in a SwiftUI application\", \"Discuss the benefits of using data visualization in a mobile application\"]', '[\"Research and review SwiftUI\'s built-in data visualization tools, such as Charts and Graphs\", \"Review industry standards for data visualization in mobile applications, such as clarity, simplicity, and user engagement\", \"Prepare examples of how data visualization can enhance user experience in a mobile application, such as displaying statistics or progress tracking\"]'),
(645, 69, 'How would you handle data analysis and processing in the SwiftUI application, and what are the best practices for implementing data visualization in a mobile context?', 'No answer provided.', 'Data Visualization', 0, '[\"Good effort.\"]', '[\"Provide a clear understanding of data analysis and processing in SwiftUI\", \"Explain best practices for data visualization in a mobile context\", \"Familiarize themselves with industry standards for data visualization in iOS applications\"]', '[\"Study SwiftUI\'s built-in data processing and analysis capabilities\", \"Research popular data visualization libraries for iOS, such as Charts or SwiftUITutorial\", \"Review Apple\'s Human Interface Guidelines for data visualization best practices in mobile applications\"]');
